column2: Sheet and data processor by Knilax (https://www.youtube.com/Knilax)

column66: Notes
Streamer was very nice and somehow actually enjoyed playing against a Legion.
Chill streamers. One survivor in the group was mildly unhappy with losing towards the end.
Poor performance on survivors' part but I also kinda sucked. They basically let me have a free win for some reason.
Meme game with 4 urban evasions.
Somehow got a merciless 4k with memey Burger King Shape on Haddonfield.
Full group of low-rank survivors.
Good killer performance lead to early suicide. Farmed until 1 gen was left.
Map offering and 4 medkits vs. Legion. Thankfully, the survivors did not perform very well.
Fun Cannibal game. Won a Red Forest match at 1 gen without gen regression.
I got absolutely destroyed and complained a lot.
Had a lag switch cheater but 4k'd anyways.
Wow. Died at 4 gens because all teammates ran into him. Took a teammate 30 seconds to figure out how to heal me.
Baby Legion. v good boy
Standard game.
Inexperienced survivors mixed with one rank one TTV.
Average Executioner and survivors. I sucked ass.
I got my 6 bear traps archive challenge done! Yee-haw
They let me snowball early game by throwing themselves at me.
Standard game.
Forgot offerings. Only got 2 successful traps so I was basically machete man. Luckily, the survivors were p chill.
I tried to make a pact with the last survivor to farm my trap challenge in exchange for the exit gate. I couldn't open the gate myself and they died an inch away from the exit. Oops.
First game since Legion P3. Hit David (s3) on hook after greeding a gen in front of me. Also hooked him in front of hatch after his friends tried to get him out and failed (leading to one more kill).
Nightmare daily ritual completed. Felt bad about the BPS while playing Nightmare so I tried to 12 hook (ended up with 10) and gave last person exit gate. Tapp (s2) was also immensely laggy.
Cheryl (s2) and Dwight (s4) teabagged a lot. They gen rushed and only went for saves when there were around two gens left. I ended up snowballing.
Wanted to try eyeball build, friends decided to also take Object. Others ended up bullying Mr. Trapper :(

HARD tunnel/camp Executioner. Looped him at shack for a gen, caged, he went straight for my cage and downed me, immediately hooked, went for my unhook, got DS'd, then camped basement and tunneled me out of it for another 2 gens. Claimed to not have tunneled/camped.
Standard game.
Standard game.
Very early hook suicide lead to a loss.
Standard game. I sucked.
NOED archive challenge. Bill (s3) booped. Survivors were surprisingly nice in post-game chat after I apologized.
Predator perk archive challenge completed.
Bloodhound perk archive challenge completed.
Predator, Bloodhound, and Shadowborn perk 3k archive challenge completed.
Two charged hatchet hits completed.
Hag daily ritual completed.
Completed Iron Maiden locker grab archive challenge. Hook suicide almost immediately. Quick win at 5 gens.
Completed 2 traps in one game archive challange. Got a nice complement from a surivor in post-game chat.
Attempted 5 traps in one game archive challenge. Got 4.
Standard game.
Nea got downed trying to do sick flips off a haybale. Stopped during the next chase to show me her cool jump. Wish I could give them a hug.
Standard game. Let Feng (s1) have exit gate.
Farmed bloodpoints with survs because 2 bps and escape cake. Jake (s4) had no idea what was happening.
Standard game. Gave Ash (s1) exit gate.
Standard game. Got accused of tunneling by Claudette (s2) because trying to save STBFL stacks. Genuinely not really sure if that counts as tunneling.

Don't let the ranks fool you, they were very good. Brought 2 BNPs and attempted to gen rush. Thank God for hats. Dwight (s3) was not given hatch at end game and complained about it in post-game chat. Tight game.
Standard game. Forgot to enter the stuff after the game. Oops.
Completed 7 heal states archive challenge. Did 6 in one game. Somehow actually looped a killer for more than 12 seconds. Also I... did it.... again. Forgot to enter stuff.
Standard game. I remembered to add the entry this time.
i forgot again :( at least i completed my 5 toolboxes consumed archive challenge.
Attempted Deathslinger chase daily ritual. I played like ass but thankfully the survivors decided to give me a free win. Christmas tree'd in basement.
Completed Deathslinger chase daily ritual. I am bad at Deathslinger.
Standard game.

Completed Legion daily ritual. All perks were level one and I apologized for using them. I had nothing else to use that wasn't ass. Didn't feel that bad because I got teabagged and complained at regardless.
Details of game included in description of survivor POV video. I've seen this cheater in a Reddit post, an OhTofu video, and my friend has also seen them in-game. ??? What???
Got farmed and died immediately. Told Trapper it was fine because I would have done the same thing. He was surprisingly nice in post-game chat.
Completed Nurse daily ritual. Feng (s1) was immersed the whole game and seemingly did nothing. Camped hatch at endgame and left.
Completed 3 medkit uses archive challenge. Nightmare with Ruin + Undying + Tinkerer, toxic in chat, TTV, tryhard mindset.... yeah. Why I don't play survivor. I wasn't nice either but still.
Survivors were very nice. I let Kate (s2) go after she failed to open the gate in front of me. Cheryl (s4) Head On'd me like 3 times.
Two key escapes.
Claudette (s4) DC'd on third hook before the animation finished. Didn't count it as a DC because it made no impact on the game.
Added one of the survivors before the game to warn them about the build. They accepted mid-game and the game ended shortly after because two hats popped. Gave hatch to Feng (s1).
Stomped early game which lead to some survivors trying to boop. I tried to respect it but I also wanted to play normally. Gave Nancy (s1) hatch.
Two survivors left, downed and hatted both next to a 99'd gen. I let let one wiggle off and do the gen, sacrifice one. Close hatch, Cheryl opens gate, head pop. I feel evil.
Standard game.
I was chilling in my house (the basement) and some random guy broke in and started trashing the place. He tried to eat my leftover (very expensive) lasagna I kept in my freezer.
Against a streamer I followed a while ago after I went against them. Chill dude.

Completed Doctor daily ritual. Survivors brought iri key with addons, BNP, purple flashlight with odd bulb and green battery. Probably one of the most stacked survivors item-wise I've seen in a while.
Wanted to show Kate the AFK David but he came back right before so they thought I was triyng to farm. Ended up farming.
Standard game. Forgot to enter the stuff.
Gave Felix (s1) exit gate and he ran away and opened hatch instead.
Dwight (s1) was nice. Forgot to enter stuff again. Was a Badham map but don't know which variant so I left it blank.
Standard game.
Standard game.
Somehow got a rank 20 Bill (s4) that started the game AFK.
They let me snowball early but I got DS'd so they reset.
One very experienced survivor. Everyone stealthed.
Meghead video for Scourge. Forgot to enter stuff.
Meghead video for Scourge. Forgot to enter stuff.
Legion DC'd almost immediately after they couldn't win a chase.
Standard game.
Immersed survivors. 3k at 5 gens with a hatch escape.
Finally have lvl 3 BBQ so trying to squeeze out as many BPs as possible.
The survivors just completely stopped doing gens as soon as 2 were left.

My start was horrendous against very competent survivors. They left Feng (s4) to die on first hook until last second. I downed her last but gave her exit gate because I sucked ass and she didn't deserve to die there.
Standard game. Trying to farm some BPs before I prestiege Executioner.
ugh
Steve (s3) was nice in post-game chat.

Rage quit early. I don't rage quit often but this was one of the most unfun games of killer I've played in a while. Everyone sucked except one survivor who was also the only one not immersed. Predropping, teabagging, clicking, Head On, ugh.
Inexperienced survivors. I let Nea (s1) have exit gate.
Completed Adept Wraith. Steam went down right when the game ended so I couldn't get info.
Completed Adept Trapper. Forgot to enter stuff again.
Completed Adept Hillbilly. Forgot to enter stuff. Again.
Completed Adept Nurse. Maybe I'll actually remember to enter the stuff next game.
Completed Adept Legion. Also AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA I KEEP FORGETTTINNNGGGG
Attempted Adept Shape. Forgot instant-downs don't count for chaser emblems. Also, I remembered to add data this time. Kinda. Entered wrong data for platforms.
Attempted Adept Executioner. I threw the end of the game for no reason.
Completed Adept Executioner.
Standard game. Forgot to equip adept perks so I played normally.
Attempted Adept Oni.
Attempted Adept Oni. Tryhard survivors. Did everything perfectly to set up for iri emblems and still didn't work. I hate playing Oni so muchhchhchccccc.
Completed Pig daily ritual. 3k + gave hatch to Feng (s1) at 5 gens.
Inexperienced survivors and a very, very early DC from Claudette (s4).
Attempted Adept Oni. Very inexperienced survivors. Forgot to enter stuff.
Completed Adept Oni. Very, very nearly failed Gatekeeper (1 gen left).
Attempted Adept Deathslinger. Three TTV lobby. Lol.
Completed Adept Nightmare.
Forgot to equip adept perks for Plague. Also I just realized how hard it's going to be to get chaser points.
Attempted Adept Plague. Forgot to enter stuff.
Standard game. Let Nancy (s1) escape via hatch.

Standard game. Was going to let Meg (s3) escape but she wiggled off and saved. Then tried to let Nea (s4) go, but she kept wiggling also. Motioned to both to stop wiggling. They said in chat they did not wiggle. ???
Standard game.

Gave me two free 4-man-downs at the start of the game and complained after the game because I didn't let them win. Complained about meta perks when they didn't do anything and also all ran meta perks. One of 'those' survivor groups definitely.
Another sweaty survivor stack. They lost to a 12-hooking Legion. Also 2 small pp builds, 3 Unbreakables. Also they brought map offering. Also they were toxic in post-game chat. You love to see it.
Found someone immediately with Undying, hit them before cleanse, then a good Punishment through a wall and... a DC. Then I found another survivor on gen, another DC. Farmed the rest of the game.
Standard game. Gave Nea (s1) hatch.
Attempted Adept Plague. Was literally like one point away from iri Malicious. All other emblems were iri.
Attempted Adept Plague. Not very great survivors and an even worse killer.
Attempted Adept Plague. Early DC. Tried to milk it but ended up having people die as slugs because they went and hid somewhere while downed and never got picked up.
Standard game. Gave Nea (s1) hatch.
Attempted Adept Plague. Another early DC. Again, tried to milk it. Jane (s1) escaped through hatch.
Standard game. Opened exit gate for Bill (s1) and Kate (s2).
Key and blueprint offering except... broken key. Also inexperienced survivors. I tryharded for no reason. Survivors were nice in post-game chat, thankfully.
Standard game. Gave David (s2) exit gate.
Survivors did everything in their power to divert all attention to the middle house gen. Gave hatch to David (s1).
Standard game.
3k + gave hatch to Quentin (s1) at 5 gens. Meg (s2) wanted to farm pallets really bad so we did that.
Semi-meme game.
Meme game.
First adrenaline vial game. Could not stop laughing.
Terrible start followed by the survivors getting cocky and me snowballing. Gave Feng (s1) exit gate.
Boring first game of the day. I sucked really bad plus nothing but W holding and predropping.
Another boring game. Same situation as last game.
Another boring game. Same situation as last game. Done for a bit. I DC'd early.
I have not been looped a single time today. I am not joking. Literally all it is today is holding W and predropping pallets. What am I doing wrong?
Macmillan map purgatory. Wow, instead of this game not being fun for me, this time it was unfun for the survivors! This game today is literal hell. 4k at 5 gens. Gave hatch to Nancy (s1).

First not cancer game of the day and it was... cancer. Survivors were annoying and accomplished nothing. Haddonfield offering. One of the survivors at the end complained a lot, saying slugging isn't necessary (lol). Today sucks.
Mirror myers has now been confirmed to work against today's braindead survivors.
Same exact survivors that I've had all day, except holding W and predropping doesn't work against Blight.
Object of Obsession Nea (s3). Accidentally clicked out too early.
Really nice survivors. I think they were a SFW. Gave exit gate to Claudette (s1).
cuties
Zarina (s4) suicided on first hook because they did a gen in front of me after being unhooked and thought I'd respect DS. Gave Nea (s1) hatch.
Standard game.
Standard game. Gave hatch to Nea (s1).
Tantrumed a lot. Let Ace (s1) crawl out.
Last minute key switch, chill streamer, and an AFK for most of the game.
Nice survivors that thanked me for not running NOED (which made me feel bad for Ruin+Undying).
Three people with 2k+ hours, including a streamer. Would have maybe lost but I got a head pop.
Inexperienced survivors and bad matchmaking. Gave Claudette (s1) hatch.
Attempted Adept Plague. Tried to go full non-vile purge Plague for more Chaser points. Obviously didn't work. SWF, clicking, small pp builds, teabagging, iri key, blueprint, map offering... ugh.
Attempted Adept Plague. Two very BS flashlights cost me the game (including one through a solid wall). Also, more of the same 3 maps on rotation. Neato burrito.
Standard game.
Standard game. Immense pressure immediately with 2 hooks and a slug. Gave exit gate to Meg (s1).
Two key escapes.
Standard game.
Completed Hillbilly daily ritual. Gave exit gate to Nea (s1).
Completed Nurse daily ritual.
Survivors decided to 'gens before friends' and lost because of it.
Survivors tried to go for saves that made no sense and I ended up snowballing.

Felt like it was physically impossible to do anything. My pressure was intense and constant and downs were frequent, but survivors were seemingly everywhere and gens would pop before I can even physically pressure them. Maybe I'm just making excuses but I feel robbed.
DC and a suicide before corrupt even ran out. Another suicide next hook, then hatch close and exit gate escape. RIP bloody party streamers.
Standard game. Thought Meg (s4) was lag switching at first but her internet was just really, really bad.
Standard game.
Adorable memesters. Farmed bloodpoints.
Was 7 away from earning the "Dream Demon" achievement, so I finished it. Gave hatch to Cheryl (s1).
Interesting post-game chat: https://pastebin.pl/view/9c0e3a0d
Quick Hag snowball.
Standard game.
Survivors made mistakes reuslting in a near instant win. Gave hatch to Feng (s1).
Would have possibly lost but Bill (s1) slow vaulted into me on accident while I was in tier 3. Snowballed from there.
Two cakes. Farmed all game.
Completed Nurse daily ritual.
Second game in a row survivors are nice in chat without reason. Wtf?
Playing horribly + puke literally never registering because reasons + bad map = lose. Thank god I'm out of puddings so I can stop playing Plague.
Standard game.
Standard game.
Inexperienced survivors. Tried to meme a lot but also wanted to play for real. Gave hatch to Meg (s1).
Survivors were inexperienced and immersed. Annoying game. Missed a lot of lunges for some reason.
I stg I thought they were all rank 20.

Completed Adept Plague. Thought I could exploit the currently terrible matchmaking. It worked! Downed Dwight (s1) right in front of hatch, which would have cost me the game. Nancy (s2) also suicided so Dwight could get hatch, which I thought would ruin the game as well.
Greeted streamer (s3) followed by game starting and DC, then streamer (unintentionally) suicides and both remaining survivors play immersed for a bit.
